{
  "stem": "14060.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 1.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we used to go with a bike to the synagogue during the week.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we-- even in later years, I must say that whilst there were some attacks on Jews, individual sort of events, on the whole in our town, it wasn't too bad, because the majority-- it was a German minority there, Volksdeutsche which they called them, and the Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they were [INAUDIBLE] at each other all the time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The small number of Jews, which was literally 3%, 4% of the population, got by because, you know, they were busy cursing each other.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But when it came to Jews, they saw eye-to-eye on it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But there was less attention given to the persecution of the Jews in our town than in some other parts of towns, where in fact, even after the war, pogroms have happened.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So there was a relative security or implied security, which under the-- illusion under which we lived.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We-- interesting part of it is that the-- the worst antagonism and origin of the constantly keeping it on a daily basis, the anti-Semitism and its results, came from the Catholic priests.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There's no question about it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I remember very clearly that it is customary, as I'm quite informed of the Catholic practices, because we lived in a Catholic religious country, that during Easter period, there are certain processions taking place.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Now I must emphasize that in that time, it wasn't a question of personal safety to walk on the streets.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was all right.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "However, when those processions were taking place-- and that was on weekdays, and I was going, let's say, at 8 o'clock in the morning to school, or coming home from school.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
